Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of citation analysis to measure interdisciplinarity in scientific literature, which is relevant to several sub-fields in computer science. Specifically, the use of community-finding algorithms and the analysis of journal-journal citation matrices suggest a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SD), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
